data.enText: The heartbeat was feeble and irregular.

data.chText: 无效的；缺乏决心的；无力的
data.enText: not effective; not showing determination or energy

data.chText: 无力的证据；站不住脚的借口；干巴巴的笑话
别那么软弱了！告诉她你不想去。
data.enText: Don't be so feeble! Tell her you don't want to go.

ex.chText: 她母亲长期患病，身体很虚弱。
ex.enText: Her mother was weak from a long illness.

ex.chText: 在戒烟问题上我意志很薄弱。
ex.enText: I'm very weak when it comes to giving up smoking.

ex.chText: 敌人力量变弱，无法再继续这场战争了。
ex.enText: The enemy became so weak that they could not go on with the war.

synonyms.bx: 最普通用词，使用范围很广，既可指身体虚弱无力的，也可引申用于力量、意志、权力、性格等方面，表示“薄弱的”、“软弱的”等。

ex.chText: 他的脉搏太弱了，摸不着。
ex.enText: His pulse was too feeble to feel.
The newborn baby gave a feeble cry.

ex.chText: 她那虚弱的胳臂无力地垂在身边。
ex.enText: Her feeble arm dropped powerless to her side.

synonyms.bx: 语气较 weak 强，尤指身体、脉搏、声音等极为虚弱而无力的。

ex.enText: The old man is growing thin and frail.

ex.chText: 她仍然感觉身体有点虚弱。
ex.enText: She was still feeling a bit frail.

ex.chText: 她虚弱的手几乎连杯子也拿不住。
ex.enText: Her frail hands could hardly hold a cup.

synonyms.bx: 多指因年迈或生病而身体瘦弱的、虚弱的、衰弱的。

example: a weak, nerveless fool, devoid of energy and promptitude"- Nathaniel Hawthorn

tr: lacking bodily or muscular strength or vitality
pathetically lacking in force or effectiveness

value.def: If you describe someone or something as feeble, you mean that they are weak.

example.ex: He told them he was old and feeble and was not able to walk so far...
example.tran: 他告诉他们，他年老体弱，不能走那么远。

example.ex: the feeble light of a tin lamp.
His left hand moved feebly at his side.
example.tran: 他的左手在身侧无力地动了一下。

value.def: If you describe someone as feeble, you are criticizing them because they are afraid of taking strong action or seem to make no effort.

example.ex: He said that the Government had been feeble.

example.tran: 一些相当软弱的传统主义者

value.def: If you describe something that someone says as feeble, you mean that it is not very good or convincing.

example.ex: This is a particularly feeble argument.
example.tran: 这个论点尤其站不住脚。

example.ex: I said 'Sorry', very feebly, feeling rather embarrassed.
example.tran: 我小声说了一句“对不起”，觉得很不好意思。
